Dodatne informacije o finalnih tekmah:

[a]. Score was 1–1 after 90 minutes and extra time. Liverpool won the penalty shoot-out 4–2.
[b]. Score was 0–0 after 90 minutes and extra time. Steaua București won the penalty shoot-out 2–0.
[c]. Score was 0–0 after 90 minutes and extra time. PSV Eindhoven won the penalty shoot-out 6–5.
[d]. Score was 0–0 after 90 minutes and extra time. Red Star Belgrade won the penalty shoot-out 5–3.
[e]. Score was 1–1 after 90 minutes and extra time. Juventus won the penalty shoot-out 4–2.
[f]. Score was 1–1 after 90 minutes and extra time. Bayern Munich won the penalty shoot-out 5–4.
[g]. Score was 0–0 after 90 minutes and extra time. A.C. Milan won the penalty shoot-out 3–2.
[h]. Score was 3–3 after 90 minutes and extra time. Liverpool won the penalty shoot-out 3–2.
[i]. Score was 1–1 after 90 minutes and extra time. Manchester United won the penalty shoot-out 6–5.
[j]. Score was 1–1 after 90 minutes and extra time. Chelsea won the penalty shoot-out 4–3.
[k]. Score was 1–1 after 90 minutes and extra time. Real Madrid won the penalty shoot-out 5–3.
[l]. The match was originally planned to be held at the Atatürk Olympic Stadium, Istanbul,
     Turkey, but was moved due to the COVID-19 pandemic in Turkey.
[m]. The 2020 final was played behind closed doors due to the COVID-19 pandemic in Europe.
[n]. The match was originally planned to be held at the Atatürk Olympic Stadium, Istanbul, Turkey, 
     but was moved due to the COVID-19 pandemic in Turkey. Previously, it was relocated from Krestovsky Stadium, Saint Petersburg, Russia.
[o]. The 2021 final was played with limited capacity due to the COVID-19 pandemic in Europe.
[p]. The match was originally planned to be held at the Krestovsky Stadium, Saint Petersburg, Russia, 
     but was moved to Saint-Denis due to the 2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine. Previously, it was relocated from Allianz Arena, Munich, Germany.
[q]. The match was originally planned to be held at the Allianz Arena, Munich, Germany, but was moved to Istanbul, with Munich hosting the 2025 final.
[r]. Includes clubs representing West Germany. No clubs representing East Germany appeared in a final.
[s]. Both Yugoslav final appearances were by clubs from SR Serbia